(40, 23, 22, 23, 66, 1, 1, 'swear by heaven', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of heaven as God''s throne, linking divine authority and the significance of oaths. Matthew references swearing by heaven, while Isaiah declares heaven as God''s throne, highlighting the sacredness of invoking God''s name.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
