(40, 23, 22, 66, 4, 2, 3, 'the throne of God', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the throne of God. In Matthew, swearing by heaven links to God''s authority, while Revelation describes the throne and Him who sits upon it.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 23, 42, 11, 42, 42, 'these ought ye to have done', 'Woes to the Pharisees', 'Both passages emphasize the hypocrisy of the Pharisees in their focus on minor tithing while neglecting more significant matters like judgment and love. This connection highlights a shared critique of their priorities in religious practice.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 23, 23, 33, 6, 8, 8, 'judgment, mercy, and faith', 'Emphasis on Justice and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of justice and mercy in one''s conduct. Matthew highlights the weightier matters of the law, including judgment and mercy, while Micah explicitly states to love mercy and do justly.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
