(40, 23, 24, 40, 27, 6, 8, 'strain at a gnat', 'Blindness to Moral Implications', 'This connection highlights the hypocrisy of the chief priests, who are concerned with the legality of blood money while ignoring the greater moral implications of their actions. Both passages emphasize a focus on minor details, such as straining at a gnat, while neglecting more significant issues, like the consequences of their decisions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
